window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>One cold December day, two men are blindsided by a hockey trade; one is the most decorated goalie in the league, while the other one is the youngest coach in the majors.</p> <p>Jethro Hale is the <i>last</i> player Coach Clay Powers wants to see on his roster, but the G.M. pulls a fast one. And it's not like he can even explain why. Nobody knows about their love affair fifteen years ago.</p> <p>Cue the all-star awkwardness, the painful memories and the reawakening of deep feelings on both sides.</p> <p>Unfortunately, their attraction still burns brightly. But it can never be. A player and a coach? The scandal would overshadow the team’s banner year.</p> <p>If only they could resist each other…</p> <p><b><i>If you love grumpy heroes, high stakes hockey, struggling single parents and smoldering kisses, grab your copy of The Last Guy on Earth.</i></b></p>"; 
